 *
 * Territory system (C rewrite) - character property tables.
 * Copyright (C) 2026 Martin Eastwood and contributors.  GPLv3 (see LICENSE).
 *
 * Territory_CharacterPropertyTable returns, for a given character "property",
 * a 256-byte table with one byte per character code (nonzero => the character
 * has that property).  The original ARM module exposed eleven such tables for
 * the Latin1 alphabet:
 *
 *   ControlTable, UppercaseTable, LowercaseTable, AlphaTable,
 *   PunctuationTable, SpaceTable, DigitTable, XDigitTable, AccentedTable,
 *   ForwardFlowTable, BackwardFlowTable
 *
 * Source of the bytes (bit-per-character DCD words, LSB = lowest char):
 *   TerritoryModule/s/Tables  (Control, Digit, XDigit; macro invocations for
 *                              Uppercase/Lowercase/Alpha/Punctuation/Space/
 *                              Accented/ForwardFlow/BackwardFlow)
 *   TerritoryModule/s/UK      (the DoXxxTable macro definitions for Latin1)
 *
 * Each DCD word covers 32 consecutive character codes, bit 0 = lowest code.
 * These have been expanded here to one C byte per character, preserving the
 * exact bits from the assembler.
 *
 * Property reason codes are taken from TerritoryManager/hdr/Territory
 * (Property_Control .. Property_BackwardFlow, allocated 0..10 in order).
 *
 * Alphabet coverage: only the Latin1 alphabet is transcribed here (it is the
 * only alphabet for which the asm defined property tables).  property_table()
 * returns the Latin1 set for ANY requested alphabet as a documented fallback;
 * callers needing non-Latin1 property data must extend this file.
 */
